'''Blerp''' was a [[web annotation]] system, launched in 2009 by RocketOn, which allowed users to overlay text, images, videos and other [[web widget|widgets]] onto web pages for other Blerp users visiting the same page to view.<ref name='gigaom'>{{cite web|url=https://gigaom.com/2009/05/13/blerp-adds-a-social-network-layer-over-the-entire-web/|title=Blerp Adds a Social Network Layer Over the Entire Web|publisher=[[GigaOm]]|date=13 May 2009|accessdate=12 June 2016}}</ref><ref name='mashable'>{{cite web|url=http://mashable.com/2009/05/13/blerp/|title=Blerp Gives Web Annotations Another Try|publisher=[[Mashable]]|date=13 May 2009|accessdate=12 June 2016}}</ref> This would allow users to start spontaneous discussions about websites.<ref name='techcrunch'>{{cite web|url=https://techcrunch.com/2009/05/13/blerp-aims-to-turn-the-web-into-one-big-forum/|title=Blerp aims to turn the web into one big forum|publisher=[[TechCrunch]]|date=13 May 2009|accessdate=12 June 2016}}</ref> Like a number of other web annotation startups, it was unsuccessful.

== See also ==
* [[Gooey]], a previous attempt at a similar idea, but without the overlay and widgets aspects
* [[Reddit]], which also allows users to share, and start discussions about, any web page, and was much more successful

