{{Infobox book | name = Women In Tech | caption = | alt = | author = [[Tarah Wheeler]] | title_orig = | orig_lang_code = | title_working = | translator = | illustrator = | cover_artist = | country = | language = | series = | subject = | genre = | published = 2016 | publisher = [[Sasquatch Books]] | media_type = | pages = 272 | awards = | isbn = 978-1-63217-066-8 | isbn_note = (Hardcover) | oclc = | dewey = | congress = | preceded_by = | followed_by = | wikisource = }}
'''''Women In Tech: Take Your Career to the Next Level with Practical Advice and Inspiring Stories ''''' is a 2016 [[anthology]] written by [[Tarah Wheeler]], an [[entrepreneur]],<ref>{{cite news |title=Books about women – past and present| url=http://www.bellinghamherald.com/entertainment/article92209657.html | publisher=Bellingham Herald | accessdate=July 29, 2016}}</ref> [[keynote]] speaker<ref>{{cite news |title=5 questions with HDC keynote Tarah Wheeler Van Vlack| url=http://siliconprairienews.com/2016/07/5-questions-hdc-keynote-tarah-wheeler-van-vlack/ | publisher=Silicon Prairie News | accessdate=July 29, 2016}}</ref> and [[scientist]],<ref name="A CEO explains">{{cite news |title=A CEO Explains How Women Can Fix Tech's Gender Problems| url=http://archive.seattleweekly.com/news/963520-129/a-ceo-explains-how-women-can | publisher=Seattle Weekly | accessdate=January 29, 2018}}</ref> and published by [[Sasquatch Books]]. The book began as a [[Kickstarter]] project, with 772 backers and $32,226 in funding.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/tarahwheelervanvlack/women-in-tech-the-book |title=Kickstarter Projects: Women In Tech The Book |accessdate=24 July 2016}}</ref>
==About== It includes advice for women in developing careers skills such as salary negotiations, networking and finding work-life balance,<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/leoking/2016/03/30/women-in-tech-book-tarah-wheeler-van-vlack/#47349efe6305 |title=How This Author Is Leveling The Playing Field For Women In Tech |accessdate=24 July 2016}}</ref> as well as personal stories from female tech professionals.<ref name="A CEO explains"/>
The book contains a foreword by [[Esther Dyson]]. In addition to Wheeler's writing, the anthology includes chapters by [[Kamilah Taylor]], [[Miah Johnson]], [[Kristin Toth Smith]], [[Keren Elazari]], [[Brianna Wu]], [[Katie Cunningham]], and [[Angie Chang]]
''[[Library Journal]]'' called ''Women in Tech'' "The essential handbook for women in technology -- engaging, practical, and inspirational."<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Scott|first=Jane|date=2016|title=Women in Tech: Take Your Career to the Next Level with Practical Advice and Inspiring Stories|url=http://search.ebscohost.com/login.aspx?direct=true&db=lfh&AN=114243060&site=ehost-live|journal=Library Journal|volume=141|issue=6|pages=104-105|subscription=yes|via=EBSCOhost}}</ref>
